    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "PORTLAND. Feb. 21.-As the re-\nsuit of widely advertised offer\nmade by Tanana mine owners for\n1000 men at S. per day, board and\ntravelling expenses, to work in the\nTanana placer fields, the Western\nFederation of Miners has placard-\ned the city appealing to the unem-\nployed not to accept the offer. The\nWestern Federation men state that\nthe importation of men into the\nTanana field is an effort to break\nthe Fairbanks, Alaska strike."
    }
  ]
